        <section address="Ephemeris">
            <title>Ephemeris</title>
            <content>
                <para>
                    In astronomy and celestial navigation, an
                    ephemeris gives the positions of astronomical objects in the sky at a given time.
                    The class
                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Graphics.Ephemeris</codeEntityReference>
                    implements an ephemeris model based on the research of Jensen et al. [1].
                </para>
                <para>
                    The <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Graphics.Ephemeris</codeEntityReference>
                    class takes the current time and the position on the Earth
                    (longitude/latitude/altitude) as input. With this info it calculates the positions
                    of the sun and moon, the moon phase and several transformation matrices which can
                    be used to
                    convert between different celestial coordinate systems. These can be used to orient
                    the stars and Milky Way cube maps correctly.
                </para>
                <para>
                    This class can also compute the direct light and ambient
                    light from the sun and the moon using a physically-based model of the Earth's
                    atmosphere and NASA data of the sun's spectrum.
                </para>
            </content>
        </section>


